cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper deals with the detection of sarcasm in social media platforms, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP. The paper also involves the analysis of multimodal posts, which includes images and text, making it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes two computational frameworks, which involve machine learning and deep learning techniques, making it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
